{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013sRi3fc2vcusETKpmoQGf7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me understand the current layout engine. The existing code already has a Sugiyama-style layered layout with:\n1. Topological sorting (Kahn's algorithm)\n2. Longest-path layer assignment\n3. Barycenter ordering for edge crossing minimization\n4. Terminal wire merging for common routes (done/abort)\n\nThe task says the graph is hard to read because \"every stage is in a vertical line and wires all overlap.\" Let me look more carefully at the issues:\n\n1. The current layout uses `nodeW = 180, nodeH = 48, layerGap = 120, nodeGap = 28` - these gaps might be too tight\n\n\n2. Edge labels at midpoints cause collisions, and the Bezier curves overlap when multiple edges route between adjacent layers since they all use the same control point formula\n\nThe main improvements needed are increasing spacing between nodes and layers, offsetting parallel edges to prevent overlap, and repositioning edge labels to avoid collisions.\n\nFor the layout engine, I should focus on increasing the spacing constants for more breathing room, offsetting edges that share source or destination nodes, using varied Bezier control points to reduce overlap, and implementing collision detection for edge labels.\n\nRefining the improved `showWorkflow` function... I'm realizing there's a mismatch here—the task header says to update documentation, but the actual request is about implementing a layout engine. Let me look at what's really being asked. The core issue is that the graph visualization needs better edge routing to prevent overlapping wires, and I should focus on implementing that rather than getting caught up in documentation updates. I need to check the actual git diff to see what changes were made to these files, then locate any documentation that needs updating to reflect the layout engine implementation.","signatu