{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TqxPW4GxLg6zT7F34LJEMm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile the final report.\n\n## Summary of Documentation Files for Web UI and Workflow Graph Visualization\n\nBased on my thorough search of the `/workspace` repository, I found all documentation files that describe or will be affected by web UI changes, especially related to workflow graph layout and the project detail page. Here's the complete list organized by relevance:\n\n### Core Web UI and Graph Visualization Documentation\n\n**1. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md` (PRIMARY)**\n- **Most relevant for your task.** This is the design document for the project detail page (`/projects/{name}`)\n- Contains detailed specifications for the **Workflow View panel** (Panel 3), which includes:\n  - Read-only DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) visualization rendered client-side\n  - Nodes rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon\n  - Edges (wires) labeled with result names\n  - **Layout engine:** \"left-to-right in topological order\" using SVG arrows, with linear column layout for initial implementation (one step per row)\n  - Upgrade path: \"proper layered layout when parallel branches are added\"\n  - Right-side drawer panel (CSS slide-in) for step details\n  - Tab navigation for container/host workflows and multiple workflows\n- Also covers orchestrator control panel and project info panel\n- Specifies new template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n- Specifies new API endpoints for workflows data\n\n**2. `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`**\n- Contains workflow DSL syntax and examples\n- References \"workflow graph\" concept throughout\n- User-facing documentation that may need updates if UI changes affect understanding\n\n**3. `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`**\n- Defines workflows as \"a named graph of steps connected by named results\"\n- Reference documentation for the workflow DSL syntax\n- May need updates if DAG visualization changes affect terminology or explanations\n\n### Related Feature and Design Documentation\n\n**4. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`**\n- Section 3: \"Web Dashboard Enhancements\" describes the landing page with project overview\n- References the project detail page as part of overall dashboard architecture\n- Mentions \"colored dots\" for run history that complement the project page\n\n**5. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`**\n- System-level architecture describing three binaries and overall design\n- References \"workflow graph\" and the graph engine\n- Foundational document for understanding the DAG model\n\n**6. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`**\n- Implementation details for core system components\n- May contain relevant backend infrastructure for graph serialization\n\n### Other Documentation Files\n\n**7. `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`**\n- Installation guide (unlikely to need updates for UI changes)\n\n**8. `/workspace/README.md`**\n- High-level project overview (unlikely to need updates)\n\n**9. `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`**\n- Project-level instructions for Claude Code (contains architecture overview)\n- References web adapter and workflow DSL\n\n**10. `/workspace/PROJECT.md`**\n- Feature roadmap mentioning \"Web Dashboard\" as a planned feature\n\n**11. `/workspace/AGENTS.md`**\n- Agent-specific documentation (unlikely to be affected)\n\n### Design Documents Not Directly Related to Graph UI\n\nThese plan documents cover other features but may have tangential relevance:\n- `2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` — host workflow concepts\n- `2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md` — configuration\n- `2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md` — initialization\n- `2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` & `2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md` — evolution feature (references DAG changes)\n- `2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md` — file layout (different \"layout\" than UI layout)\n- `2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md` — wire mapping (DAG edge details)\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings for Your Web UI Change\n\nThe primary document you need to update is **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** under **Panel 3: Workflow View**, specifically the \"### DAG rendering\" section (lines 133-137), which currently specifies:\n\n- Client-side layout with no heavy library\n- Left-to-right topological order\n- SVG arrows connecting boxes\n- Linear column layout (one step per row) for initial implementation\n- Planned upgrade to \"proper layered layout when parallel branches are added\"\n\nYou may also need to update `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` and `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` if your layout changes affect how the workflow graph should be understood by end users."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af85aecdec2287da3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48813\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 38881</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b222aa3d-4bbf-440c-993c-c83ddd6bf5b6","uuid":"552e6847-af51-4e79-8fef-140651dd9541","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the /workspace repository to find all documentation files (*.md, docs/**) that might describe the web UI, workflow graph visualization, layout engine, or the project detail page. I need to know which docs exist that might need updating after a web UI change to the workflow graph layout. Search thoroughly in docs/, and any other locations for markdown files. Report all file paths found and a brief summary of their contents related to the web UI or graph.","agentId":"af85aecdec2287da3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile the final report.\n\n## Summary of Documentation Files for Web UI and Workflow Graph Visualization\n\nBased on my thorough search of the `/workspace` repository, I found all documentation files that describe or will be affected by web UI changes, especially related to workflow graph layout and the project detail page. Here's the complete list organized by relevance:\n\n### Core Web UI and Graph Visualization Documentation\n\n**1. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md` (PRIMARY)**\n- **Most relevant for your task.** This is the design document for the project detail page (`/projects/{name}`)\n- Contains detailed specifications for the **Workflow View panel** (Panel 3), which includes:\n  - Read-only DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) visualization rendered client-side\n  - Nodes rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon\n  - Edges (wires) labeled with result names\n  - **Layout engine:** \"left-to-right in topological order\" using SVG arrows, with linear column layout for initial implementation (one step per row)\n  - Upgrade path: \"proper layered layout when parallel branches are added\"\n  - Right-side drawer panel (CSS slide-in) for step details\n  - Tab navigation for container/host workflows and multiple workflows\n- Also covers orchestrator control panel and project info panel\n- Specifies new template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n- Specifies new API endpoints for workflows data\n\n**2. `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`**\n- Contains workflow DSL syntax and examples\n- References \"workflow graph\" concept throughout\n- User-facing documentation that may need updates if UI changes affect understanding\n\n**3. `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`**\n- Defines workflows as \"a named graph of steps connected by named results\"\n- Reference documentation for the workflow DSL syntax\n- May need updates if DAG visualization changes affect terminology or explanations\n\n### Related Feature and Design Documentation\n\n**4. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`**\n- Section 3: \"Web Dashboard Enhancements\" describes the landing page with project overview\n- References the project detail page as part of overall dashboard architecture\n- Mentions \"colored dots\" for run history that complement the project page\n\n**5. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`**\n- System-level architecture describing three binaries and overall design\n- References \"workflow graph\" and the graph engine\n- Foundational document for understanding the DAG model\n\n**6. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`**\n- Implementation details for core system components\n- May contain relevant backend infrastructure for graph serialization\n\n### Other Documentation Files\n\n**7. `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`**\n- Installation guide (unlikely to need updates for UI changes)\n\n**8. `/workspace/README.md`**\n- High-level project overview (unlikely to need updates)\n\n**9. `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`**\n- Project-level instructions for Claude Code (contains architecture overview)\n- References web adapter and workflow DSL\n\n**10. `/workspace/PROJECT.md`**\n- Feature roadmap mentioning \"Web Dashboard\" as a planned feature\n\n**11. `/workspace/AGENTS.md`**\n- Agent-specific documentation (unlikely to be affected)\n\n### Design Documents Not Directly Related to Graph UI\n\nThese plan documents cover other features but may have tangential relevance:\n- `2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` — host workflow concepts\n- `2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md` — configuration\n- `2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md` — initialization\n- `2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` & `2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md` — evolution feature (references DAG changes)\n- `2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md` — file layout (different \"layout\" than UI layout)\n- `2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md` — wire mapping (DAG edge details)\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings for Your Web UI Change\n\nThe primary document you need to update is **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** under **Panel 3: Workflow View**, specifically the \"### DAG rendering\" section (lines 133-137), which currently specifies:\n\n- Client-side layout with no heavy library\n- Left-to-right topological order\n- SVG arrows connecting boxes\n- Linear column layout (one step per row) for initial implementation\n- Planned upgrade to \"proper layered layout when parallel branches are added\"\n\nYou may also need to update `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` and `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` if your layout changes affect how the workflow graph should be understood by end users."}],"totalDurationMs":38881,"totalTokens":48813,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":436,"cache_read_input_tokens":47207,"output_tokens":1165,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":436},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
